genresAdvancedInfo.name: icelandic traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Icelandic traditional music is deeply rooted in the country's history and culture, with influences from Viking and Nordic traditions. It features haunting melodies and intricate arrangements, often performed on traditional instruments such as the langspil and fiðla. The lyrics often tell stories of Iceland's landscape, mythology, and daily life.
